    "description": "Join the Sports Authority India Capital India family as a Department Manager in Bengaluru. We believe in empowering our employees with the tools, training, and environment they need to succeed.\n\nAbout Sports Authority India Capital India:\nSports Authority India Capital India is a leading organization in the Remote sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Monitor inventory levels and coordinate replenishment activities\n• Conduct regular stock audits and prevent pilferage\n• Handle customer queries, complaints, and escalations effectively\n• Implement promotional activities and in-store campaigns\n• Ensure visual merchandising standards are maintained at all times\n• Manage shrinkage and reduce stock discrepancies\n• Ensure compliance with company policies and retail regulations\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• B.Com / M.Com / MBA Finance\n• 6-10 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Omnichannel Retail\n• Proficiency in Customer Service\n• Proficiency in POS Systems\n• Proficiency in Category Management\n• Proficiency in Supply Chain\n• Proficiency in Planogram\n• Proficiency in Sales Techniques\n• Proficiency in Visual Merchandising\n\nWork Mode: Remote - Work from anywhere in India\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Referral bonus program\n• Meal coupons and food allowance\n• International travel opportunities for senior roles\n• Life and accident insurance\n• Transportation and conveyance allowance\n• Annual performance appraisal\n• Salary Range: 12 LPA - 25 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Bengaluru, Karnataka, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Sports Authority India Capital India!",
